kawa Sneaker Bunko\n| published       = April 1, 2016\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| title           = Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Bakuen o!\n| author          = Natsume Akatsuki\n| illustrator     = Kasumi Morino\n| publisher       = [[Media Factory]]\n| demographic     = ''[[Sh\u014dnen manga|Sh\u014dnen]]''\n| magazine        = [[Monthly Comic Alive]]\n| first           = May 27, 2016\n| last            = \n| volumes         = \n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = light novel\n| title           = Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! Extra: Ano Orokamono ni mo Kyakkou o!\n| author          = Hirukuma\n| illustrator     = Y\u016bki Hagure\n| publisher       = Kadokawa Shoten\n| demographic     = Male\n| imprint         = Kadokawa Sneaker Bunko\n| first           = August 1, 2017\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 4\n| volume_list     = List of KonoSuba volumes#Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku wo! Extra - Ano Orokamono ni mo Kyakkou wo!\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Game\n| title           = Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! -Kono Yokubukai Game ni Shinpan o!-\n| developer       = [[5pb.]]\n| publisher       = 5pb.<br />[[Ubisoft]]\n| genre           = [[Visual novel]]\n| platforms       = [[PlayStation Vita]], [[PlayStation 4]]\n| released        = September 7, 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gematsu.com/2017/05/konosuba-game-ps4-ps-vita-launches-september-7-japan|title=KonoSuba game for PS4, PS Vita launches September 7 in Japan - Gematsu|author=|date=10 May 2017|website=gematsu.com|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Other\n| title           = Film\n| content         =\n*''[[KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World! Legend of Crimson]]''\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''''KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World!'''''|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092!|Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o!|literally \"A blessing to this wonderful world!\"|lead=yes}}<!--Please do not remove or change the title to its Japanese equivalent without providing the English translation. Wikipedia guidelines dictates we must use the English language title. --> is a Japanese [[light novel]] series written by Natsume Akatsuki. The series follows a boy who is [[isekai|sent to a fantasy world]] following his death, forming a dysfunctional party with a goddess, a wizard, and a crusader to fight against monsters. Beginning as a [[web novel]] series published on [[Sh\u014dsetsuka ni Nar\u014d]] between December 2012 and October 2013, the series was revised into a printed [[light novel]] series with illustrations by Kurone Mishima, which began publication under [[Kadokawa Shoten]]'s ''[[Kadokawa Sneaker Bunko]]'' [[imprint (trade name)|imprint]] from October 2013.\n\nA [[manga]] adaptation, illustrated by Masahito Watari and Joseph Yokobori, began serialization in [[Fujimi Shobo]]'s ''[[Monthly Dragon Age]]'' magazine from October 2014. A radio [[drama CD]] was released by HobiRecords in March 2015, and an [[anime]] television adaptation by [[Studio Deen]] aired in Japan between January and March 2016. A second season of the anime aired between January and March 2017.<ref name=\"S2Anc\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-03-16/konosuba-anime-gets-2nd-season/.99855|title=KonoSuba Anime Gets 2nd Season|date=March 16, 2016|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=March 16, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"s2 Air date\">{{cite web|url=http://nagamedigital.com/2016/11/14/konosuba-season-2-release-date/|title=KONOSUBA SEASON 2 GETS OFFICIAL RELEASE DATE, PV AND KEY VISUAL|date=November 14, 2016|website=nagamedigital.com|accessdate=November 14, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114232041/http://nagamedigital.com/2016/11/14/konosuba-season-2-release-date/|archive-date=November 14, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"s2 January\">{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2016-06-24/konosuba-tv-anime-2nd-season-premieres-in-january/.103579 |title=KonoSuba TV Anime's 2nd Season Premieres in January |date=June 24, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=June 24, 2016 }}</ref> A spin-off light novel series, ''Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Bakuen o!'', began publication from July 2014. Both the light novels and the manga are licensed in North America by [[Yen Press]]. An anime film adaptation by [[J.C.Staff]] titled ''[[KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World! Legend of Crimson]]'' premiered on August 30, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/anime/konosuba-season-3-release-date-new-anime-teased-by-kazuma-megumin-voice-actors-fans-hope-for-bakuen-anime-konosuba-movie-or-ova-3-light-novel-spoilers/|title=KonoSuba Season 3 release date: New anime teased by Kazuma, Megumin voice actors! Fans hope for KonoSuba movie based on Bakuen books, OVA 3 [Light Novel Spoilers]|publisher=[[Monsters and Critics]]|date=October 23, 2018|accessdate=October 23, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n<!-- Note, as the light novel is the PRIMARY work, this plot summary should be written for the light novel, not the anime or manga. -->\n{{See also|List of KonoSuba characters}}\nFollowing an untimely and embarrassing death, Kazuma Sat\u014d, a Japanese teenager [[hikikomori|shut-in]] [[NEET]], meets a goddess named Aqua, who offers to reincarnate him in a [[parallel universe (fiction)|parallel world]] with [[Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|MMORPG]] elements, where he can go on adventures and battle monsters. Despite being offered a superpowered item or ability to use in this new world, Kazuma, following some provocation, chooses Aqua herself to accompany him to the town of Axel, quickly finding her absent-mindedness to be less than beneficial.{{ref|LN|LN 1.P}} With Aqua unable to return to the afterlife until the [[Dark Lord (fiction)|Devil King]] is defeated, the two form a [[Party (role-playing games)|party]] and recruit two other members; an explosion-obsessed magician named Megumin and a masochistic crusader named Darkness.{{ref|LN|LN 1.2.4}} Due to the party's dysfunctional abilities, Kazuma quickly gives up on the idea of defeating the Devil King and tries to live a luxurious lifestyle, only to find the circumstances of his daily life are forcing him and his party to encounter and battle the Devil King's generals.{{ref|LN|LN 2.3}}\n\n==Media==\n===Novels===\n{{See also|List of KonoSuba volumes#Light novels}}\nThe original [[web novel]] series written by Natsume Akatsuki was published on Syosetu between December 2012 and October 2013.<ref name=\"Syosetu\">{{cite web| archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130827082350/http://ncode.syosetu.com/n7145bl/| archivedate=August 27, 2013| url=http://ncode.syosetu.com/n7145bl/| title=KonoSuba web novel| publisher=Syosetu| language=Japanese| accessdate=February 8, 2016}}</ref> The author also wrote a side story featuring Wiz and Vanir.<ref name=\"WN Side\">{{cite web| archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130729143507/http://ncode.syosetu.com/n7364bo/| archivedate=July 29, 2013| url=http://ncode.syosetu.com/n7145bl/| title=The Masked Demon's Dream Watching| publisher=Syosetu| language=Japanese| accessdate=February 8, 2016}}</ref> Akatsuki, who enjoyed playing fantasy video games like ''[[Wizardry]]'' and ''[[Final Fantasy]]'', also derived much of ''KonoSuba''{{'s}} fantasy elements from [[tabletop role-playing game]]s.<ref name=\"Akatsuki interview\">{{cite web|last=Green|first=Scott|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/04/26-1/the-anime-man-interviews-konosuba-creator|title=The Anime Man Interviews \"Konosuba\" Creator|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=April 26, 2017|accessdate=September 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\nA [[light novel]] version with illustrations by Kurone Mishima began release under [[Kadokawa Shoten]]'s [[Kadokawa Sneaker Bunko]] [[Imprint (trade name)|imprint]] from October 1, 2013,<ref name=\"LN1\">{{cite web| url=http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321307000151| script-title=ja:\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01| publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]]| accessdate=May 30, 2015| language=Japanese| title=Archived copy| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150530122639/http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321307000151| archive-date=May 30, 2015| url-status=dead}}</ref> with seventeen volumes released as of May 1, 2020.<ref name=\"LN13\">{{cite web| url=http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321706000257| script-title=ja:\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092!13| publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]]| accessdate=January 20, 2018| language=Japanese| title=Archived copy| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030003500/http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321706000257| archive-date=October 30, 2017| url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"LN16\">{{cite web |title=\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff0116 \u8131\u8d70\u5973\u795e\u3001\u30b4\u30fc\u30db\u30fc\u30e0\uff01 |url=https://sneakerbunko.jp/product/konosuba/321904000247.html |publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]] |accessdate=December 10, 2019 |language=Japanese}}</ref> The light novel diverges significantly from the web novel's plot from the sixth volume onwards,{{citation needed|date=August 2017}} and also features changes to the characters' ages. The final book in the series, Volume 17, contains an After Story in the Afterward section that extends the ending of the original web novel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/anime/konosuba-ending-light-novel-volume-17-after-story-natsume-akatsuki-konosuba-gods-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-books/|title=KonoSuba ending with light novel Volume 17: After story to finish Natsume Akatsuki\u2019s KonoSuba: God\u2019s Blessing on this Wonderful World! books|publisher=[[Monsters and Critics]]|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\nA Megumin-focused [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] light novel series, also written and illustrated by Akatsuki and Mishima respectively, titled {{nihongo3|lit. \"Give Explosions to This Wonderful World!\"|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u7206\u7114\u3092\uff01|Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Bakuen o!}} and takes place a year prior to the main series, began release from July 1, 2014, with three volumes released as of June 1, 2015.<ref name=\"MegLN1\">{{cite web|url=http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321403000163|script-title=ja:\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u7206\u7114\u3092\uff01|publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]]|accessdate=June 6, 2015|language=Japanese|title=Archived copy|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150319035638/http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321403000163|archive-date=March 19, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> A sequel novel was released December 28, 2016,<ref name=\"MegSequelLN1\">{{cite web |url=http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321607000363 |script-title=ja:\u7d9a\u30fb\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u7206\u7114\u3092\uff01 |publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]] |accessdate=February 11, 2017 |language=Japanese |title=Archived copy |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180118182424/http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321607000363 |archive-date=January 18, 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref> named {{nihongo3|lit. \"Sequel: Give Explosions to This Wonderful World!\"|\u7d9a\u30fb\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u7206\u7114\u3092\uff01|Zoku: Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Bakuen o!}}. Another spin-off featuring Vanir was published on April 1, 2016, called {{nihongo3|lit. \"Consulting with the Masked Devil!\"|\u3053\u306e\u4eee\u9762\u306e\u60aa\u9b54\u306b\u76f8\u8ac7\u3092\uff01|Kono Kamen no Akuma ni S\u014ddan o!}}.<ref name=\"VanLN1\">{{cite web|url=http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321601000557|script-title=ja:\u3053\u306e\u4eee\u9762\u306e\u60aa\u9b54\u306b\u76f8\u8ac7\u3092\uff01|publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]]|accessdate=June 30, 2016|language=Japanese|title=Archived copy|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160402060707/http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321601000557|archive-date=April 2, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nA third spin-off series titled {{nihongo3|lit. \"Bless Me in This Wonderful World! Extra: Attention Also to That Fool!\"|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u30a8\u30af\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9 \u3042\u306e\u611a\u304b\u8005\u306b\u3082\u811a\u5149\u3092\uff01|Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! Extra Ano Orokamono ni mo Kyakkou o!}} began publication on August 1, 2017. It is written by Hirukuma and illustrated by Uihime Hagure, and features Dust as the central character.<ref name=\"ExLN1\">{{cite web|url=http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321703000426|title=\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u30a8\u30af\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9 \u3042\u306e\u611a\u304b\u8005\u306b\u3082\u811a\u5149\u3092\uff01|publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]]|accessdate=January 29, 2018|language=Japanese|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030003504/http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321703000426|archive-date=October 30, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> The second volume was released on December 1, 2017.<ref name=\"ExLN2\">{{cite web|url=http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321703000427|title=\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u30a8\u30af\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9 \u3042\u306e\u611a\u304b\u8005\u306b\u3082\u811a\u5149\u3092\uff012|publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]]|accessdate=January 29, 2018|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n[[Yen Press]] announced on May 20, 2016 that it had licensed the light novels for release in North America.<ref name=\"Yen Press\">{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-05-20/yen-press-licenses-konosuba-death-march-to-the-parallel-world-rhapsody-manga-light-novels/.102332 |title=Yen Press Licenses Konosuba, Death March to the Parallel World Rhapsody Manga, Light Novels |date=May 20, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=May 20, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170702032320/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-05-20/yen-press-licenses-konosuba-death-march-to-the-parallel-world-rhapsody-manga-light-novels/.102332|archivedate=July 2, 2017}}</ref> The first volume was released in conjunction with the second manga volume on February 21, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://yenpress.com/2017/02/konosuba-gods-blessing-on-this-hilariously-frustrating-world/|title=Konosuba: God's Blessing on This Hilariously Frustrating World|work=[[Yen Press]]|date=February 21, 2017|accessdate=August 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Manga===\n{{See also|List of KonoSuba volumes#Manga}}\nA [[manga]] adaption of ''KonoSuba'' illustrated by Masahito Watari began serialization in the October 2014 issue of [[Fujimi Shobo]]'s ''[[Monthly Dragon Age]]'' magazine on September 9, 2014.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://natalie.mu/comic/news/125663| title=''Omamori Himari'', Milan Matra's New Series| publisher=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]| date=September 9, 2014| accessdate=October 30, 2015| language=Japanese}}</ref> Eight ''tank\u014dbon'' volumes have been released as of May 2019. A spin-off manga, ''A Spotlight For (Even) This fool! Gifting this Wonderful World with Blessings! Extra'', was released as a bundle with the twelfth light novel volume. Written and illustrated by Kuma Hiru and Hagure Yuki, respectively, it follows the story of Dust, who finds himself in trouble with Vanir over selling stolen products.<ref>{{cite web|last=Green|first=Scott|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/06/16/konosuba-anticipates-humiliation-a-new-ova-and-cover-previews|title=\"Konosuba\" Anticipates Humiliation, a New OVA and Cover Previews|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=June 16, 2017|accessdate=September 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\nYen Press announced its acquisition of the manga adaptation at the same time that it licensed the original light novels.<ref name=\"Yen Press\"/>\n\n===Anime===\n{{See also|List of KonoSuba episodes}}\nAn [[anime]] television adaptation by [[Studio Deen]]<ref name=\"AnimeAnnouncement\">{{cite web| url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-05-25/kono-subarashii-sekai-ni-shukufuku-o-alternate-world-comedy-light-novels-get-tv-anime/.88540| title=''KonoSuba'' TV Anime Announcement| publisher=[[Anime News Network]]| date=May 25, 2015| accessdate=May 25, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170626203637/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-05-25/kono-subarashii-sekai-ni-shukufuku-o-alternate-world-comedy-light-novels-get-tv-anime/.88540|archivedate=June 26, 2017}}</ref> aired on [[Tokyo MX]] between January 14, 2016, and March 16, 2016;<ref name=\"Networks\">{{cite web| url=http://konosuba.com/1st/onair/| title=''KonoSuba'' Network Information|  publisher=KonoSuba.com| language=Japanese| accessdate=January 29, 2016|quote=TOKYO MX &ndash; 1\u670813\u65e5\u3088\u308a\u6bce\u9031\u6c34\u66dc &ndash; 25:05 \uff5e 25:35}}</ref> later broadcasting on eight other networks and several [[video on demand]] [[streaming media|streaming networks]].<ref name=\"Networks\"/> The series was simulcast by [[Crunchyroll]] in several regions such as North America,<ref name=\"Crunchyroll\">{{cite web| url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-01-12/crunchyroll-to-stream-konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-anime/.97499| title=Crunchyroll to Stream KonoSuba| date=January 12, 2016| publisher=[[Anime News Network]]| accessdate=February 1, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170728231301/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-01-12/crunchyroll-to-stream-konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-anime/.97499|archivedate=July 28, 2017}}</ref> and by [[AnimeLab]] in Australia.<ref name=\"AnimeLab\">{{cite web| url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-22/new-titles-for-animelab-2016-winter-simulcast-season/.96781| title=New Titles for AnimeLab 2016 Winter Simulcast Season| date=December 21, 2015| publisher=[[Anime News Network]]| accessdate=February 8, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170729011400/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-22/new-titles-for-animelab-2016-winter-simulcast-season/.96781|archivedate=July 29, 2017}}</ref>  The series was directed by Takaomi Kanasaki and written by [[Makoto Uezu]] with character designs by Koichi Kikuta.<ref name=\"AnimeAnnouncement\" /> An [[original video animation]] (OVA) was bundled with the ninth light novel of ''KonoSuba'' in June 2016.<ref name=\"OVA1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-21/kono-subarashii-sekai-ni-shukufuku-o-light-novel-bundles-original-anime-blu-ray/.96791| title=''KonoSuba'' Light Novel Bundles Original Anime Blu-ray| publisher=[[Anime News Network]]| date=December 21, 2015| accessdate=December 21, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170726160432/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-21/kono-subarashii-sekai-ni-shukufuku-o-light-novel-bundles-original-anime-blu-ray/.96791|archivedate=July 26, 2017}}</ref> The anime's opening theme is \"Fantastic Dreamer\" by [[Machico (singer)|Machico]] while the ending theme is {{nihongo|\"Ch\u012bsana B\u014dken-sha\"|\u3061\u3044\u3055\u306a\u5192\u967a\u8005|lit.\"Little Adventurer\"}} performed by [[Sora Amamiya]], [[Rie Takahashi]], and [[Ai Kayano]].<ref name=\"Staff\">{{cite web| url=http://konosuba.com/1st/staff_cast/| title=KonoSuba anime staff| publisher=KonoSuba.com| language=Japanese| accessdate=January 31, 2016}}</ref> On January 7, 2019, Crunchyroll announced that the series would receive an English dub.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-01-07/crunchyroll-to-stream-konosuba-anime-dubbed-in-english-spanish-portuguese/.141729|last=Ressler|first=Karen|title=Crunchyroll to Stream Konosuba Anime Dubbed in English, Spanish, Portuguese|date=January 7, 2019|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]| accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref> The season 1 dub made its debut on January 25, 2019,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/konosuba-finally-has-an-english-dub-and-heres-wher/1100-6464212/|title=Konosuba Finally Has An English Dub, And Here's Where You Can Watch It|website=GameSpot|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-07}}</ref> with the second season's dub being released on February 25, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|last=Luster|first=Joseph|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2020/02/15-1/konosuba-season-2-dub-comes-to-crunchyroll-on-february-25|title=KONOSUBA Season 2 Dub Comes to Crunchyroll on February 25|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=February 15, 2020|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref> [[Discotek Media]] will release the first season on Blu-ray in North America, with the release scheduled for May 25, 2020.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=discotekmedia|author=Discotek Media|author-link=Discotek Media|number=1237437365527949312|date=March 10, 2020|title=Today, we woke up to the amazing and wonderful news that WE, Discotek Media, are releasing Konosuba: God's Blessing On this Wonderful World season 1 on Blu-Ray this May!! The OVA is included, too!!! https://rightstufanime.com/Konosuba-Season-1-OVA-Blu-ray|accessdate=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe series was animated by Koichi Kikuta and Momoka Komatsu, with the former working on odd-numbered episodes and the latter on even-numbered. While Komatsu's character designs closely resembled those of the light novels and had more attractive appearances, Kikuta based his designs on children's shows like ''[[Pok\u00e9mon (anime)|Pok\u00e9mon]]'' as he felt ''KonoSuba''{{'s}} story was similar to those found in such shows.<ref name=\"Interview with Koichi Kikuta\" />\n\nA second season aired between January 12, 2017, and March 16, 2017.<ref name=\"S2Anc\"/><ref name=\"s2 Air date\"/><ref name=\"s2 January\" /> The second season's opening theme is \"Tomorrow\" by Machico, and the ending theme is {{nihongo|\"Ouchi ni Kaeritai\"|\u304a\u5bb6\u306b\u5e30\u308a\u305f\u3044|lit.\"Want to Go Home\"}} by Amamiya, Takahashi, and Kayano.<ref>{{cite web|title=KonoSuba 2 Anime's Promo Video Previews Machico's Opening Theme|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-12-12/konosuba-2-anime-promo-video-previews-machico-opening-theme/.109782|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=December 13, 2016|date=December 12, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731160957/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-12-12/konosuba-2-anime-promo-video-previews-machico-opening-theme/.109782|archivedate=July 31, 2017}}</ref> A second OVA was bundled with the twelfth volume of ''KonoSuba'' in July 2017.<ref name=\"OVA2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-12-26/konosuba-light-novel-to-bundle-original-anime-blu-ray/.110350|title=KonoSuba Light Novel to Bundle Original Anime Blu-ray|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 26, 2016|accessdate=December 26, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731004431/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-12-26/konosuba-light-novel-to-bundle-original-anime-blu-ray/.110350|archivedate=July 31, 2017}}</ref> On July 25, 2017, [[Jun Fukushima]] and Takahashi, the voice actors of Kazuma and Megumin respectively, announced plans for a new ''KonoSuba'' anime project, later revealed to be a new movie, ''[[KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World! Legend of Crimson]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-07-25/konosuba-comedy-fantasy-anime-gets-new-anime-project/.119285 |title=KonoSuba Comedy Fantasy Anime Gets New Anime Project |date=July 25, 2017 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=January 20, 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Green|first=Scott|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/07/25-1/new-konosuba-anime-project-announced|title=New \"Konosuba\" Anime Project Announced|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=July 25, 2017|accessdate=August 26, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn October 6, 2018, it was announced that characters from ''KonoSuba'' would appear in ''[[Isekai Quartet]]'', a crossover anime also featuring characters from ''[[Re:Zero \u2212 Starting Life in Another World]]'', ''[[Overlord (novel series)|Overlord]]'', and ''[[The Saga of Tanya the Evil]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-10-06/new-isekai-quartet-anime-project-crosses-over-overlord-re-zero-tanya-konosuba-franchises/.137803 |title=New Isekai Quartet Anime Project Crosses Over Overlord, Re:Zero, Tanya, Konosuba Franchises |date=October 6, 2018 |website=Anime News Network |accessdate=October 14, 2018 }}</ref>\n\n===Film===\n{{see also|KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World! Legend of Crimson}}\nOn June 25, 2018, a film adaptation was announced to be in development at [[J.C.Staff]]. The cast and staff reprised their roles from the TV series.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hodgkins |first1=Crystalyn |title=Konosuba - God's Blessing on This Wonderful World! Anime Gets Film Project |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-06-25/konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-anime-gets-film-project/.133376 |website=Anime News Network |accessdate=June 25, 2018 |date=June 25, 2018}}</ref> The film is titled {{nihongo|''KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World! Crimson Legend''|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u7d05\u4f1d\u8aac|Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! Kurenai Densetsu}},<ref>{{cite web |title=\u300e\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u7d05\u4f1d\u8aac\u300f\u30c6\u30a3\u30b6\u30fc\u30d3\u30b8\u30e5\u30a2\u30eb\u516c\u958b\uff01 |url=https://konosuba.com/2nd/news/?mode=detail&id=20181104_1 |publisher=[[Kadokawa Corporation]] |accessdate=November 5, 2018 |language=Japanese |date=November 5, 2018}}</ref> and it premiered in Japan on August 30, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hodgkins |first1=Crystalyn|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2018-10-20/konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-anime-film-opens-in-2019/.138430|title=KONOSUBA - God's blessing on this wonderful world! Anime Film Opens in 2019|date=October 20, 2018|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=October 20, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Pineda |first1=Rafael Antonio|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-04-25/konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-anime-film-reveals-song-artists-august-debut/.146140|title=KONOSUBA - God's blessing on this wonderful world! Anime Film Reveals Song Artists, August Debut|date=April 25, 2019|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=April 25, 2019}}</ref> Crunchyroll began streaming the English subtitles and English dub version in March and April of 2020, respectively.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Frye|first1=Patrick |title=Crunchyroll streaming KonoSuba: Legend of Crimson English dub/sub for movie release in 2020 |url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/anime/crunchyroll-streaming-konosuba-legend-of-crimson-english-dub-sub-movie-release-date-2020/ |website=[[Monsters and Critics]] |accessdate=March 10, 2020 |date=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Video games===\nA PC [[video game]] developed by game creator Tachi, titled {{nihongo|''Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! In The Life''|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01in the life}}, is bundled with the first Blu-ray Disc/DVD volume of the anime series on March 25, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-02-13/konosuba-1st-blu-ray-dvd-to-include-pc-game/.98637 |title=KonoSuba's 1st Blu-ray/DVD to Include PC Game |date=February 13, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802002325/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-02-13/konosuba-1st-blu-ray-dvd-to-include-pc-game/.98637|archivedate=August 2, 2017}}</ref> The game is developed using the software [[RPG Maker VX]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Blu-ray\u9650\u5b9a\u7248&DVD\u9650\u5b9a\u7248\u3000\u7b2c1\u5dfb\u3000\u8d85\u8c6a\u83ef5\u5927\u7279\u5178\uff01\uff01|url=http://konosuba.com/1st/bd/?mode=detail&id=bd1|website=\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u300e\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u300f\u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=August 21, 2016|language=Japanese}}</ref> Another video game, created by Team Ladybug and Krobon, titled ''KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World! Revival of Beldia'' ({{nihongo|''Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! Fukatsu no Verdier''|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u5fa9\u6d3b\u306e\u30d9\u30eb\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2}}) is bundled with the limited edition of first Blu-ray Disc/DVD volume of the anime series' second season and was released on April 28, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u300c\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\uff12\u300d Blu-ray & DVD \u7b2c1\u5dfb|url=http://konosuba.com/bd/?mode=detail&id=bd1|website=\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u300e\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff012\u300f\u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8|accessdate=March 30, 2017|language=Japanese}}</ref> The game is a [[side-scrolling video game|side-scroller]] with gameplay resembling the ''[[Mega Man (video game)|Mega Man]]'' series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/2017/02/01/konosubas-season-2-limited-blu-ray-bonus-sweet-mega-man-style-side-scroller/|title=KonoSuba's Season 2 Limited Blu-ray Bonus Is A Sweet Mega Man-Style Side-Scroller|publisher=Siliconera|date=February 1, 2017|accessdate=August 25, 2017}}</ref>\n\nA visual novel adaptation for [[PlayStation Vita]] and [[PlayStation 4]], ''KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World! Judgment on this Greedy Game!'' ({{nihongo|''Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! -Kono Yokubukai Game ni Shinpan o!-''|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01 -\u3053\u306e\u6b32\u6df1\u3044\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u306b\u5be9\u5224\u3092\uff01-}}), was developed by [[5pb.]], published by [[Ubisoft]] and was released in Japan on September 7, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/2017/05/10/konosubas-new-game-releases-september-7-japan-comes-bonus-konosuba-shooting-game/v|title=KonoSuba's New Game Releases September 7 In Japan, Comes With Bonus KonoSuba Shooting Game|work=Siliconera|date=May 10, 2017|accessdate=August 26, 2017}}</ref> The game features an original story, in which Kazuma discovers a cursed ring that allows him to steal the underwear of others near him. He learns the only way to undo the curse would be through raising enough money. ''Judgment on this Greedy Game!'' introduces an \"Underwear Judgment\" system, where the player assists Kazuma in returning lost underwear to their rightful owner.<ref>{{cite web|last=Romano|first=Sal|title=KonoSuba game launches for PS4 and PS Vita this summer in Japan|url=https://gematsu.com/2017/03/konosuba-game-launches-ps4-ps-vita-summer-japan|publisher=Gematsu|accessdate=March 30, 2017}}</ref> Like the anime, Machico performed the opening \"Million Smile\", while Amamiya, Takahashi, and Kayano sang the game's ending theme \"101 Pikime no Hitsuji\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Green|first=Scott|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/07/23/hear-cast-and-machico-sing-konosuba-game-themes|title=Hear Cast And Machico Sing \"Konosuba\" Game Themes|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=July 23, 2017|accessdate=August 26, 2017}}</ref>\n\nA mobile game titled {{nihongo|''Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! Fantastic Days''|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u30d5\u30a1\u30f3\u30bf\u30b9\u30c6\u30a3\u30c3\u30af\u30c7\u30a4\u30ba}} was released for iOS and Android devices on February 27, 2020.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u3010\u516c\u5f0f\u3011\u300a\u597d\u8a55\u914d\u4fe1\u4e2d\u300b\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u30d5\u30a1\u30f3\u30bf\u30b9\u30c6\u30a3\u30c3\u30af\u30c7\u30a4\u30ba\uff08\u3053\u306e\u30d5\u30a1\u30f3\uff09 |url=https://konosubafd.jp/ |accessdate=March 25, 2020 |language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n===Audio CDs===\nA radio [[drama CD]], featuring a different voice cast to the anime, was released by HobiRecords on March 1, 2015.<ref name=\"Drama CD\">{{cite web| url=https://www.toranoana.jp/info/dojin/konosuba/| title=KonoSuba Drama CD| publisher=[[Comic Toranoana]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=January 29, 2016}}</ref> A second drama CD, along with an original soundtrack by Kouda Masato and a [[character song]] album, was released in March 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://otakumode.com/news/5891ab30e088942e19129b4f/March-Is-KonoSuba-Month-New-Original-Soundtrack-Drama-CD-Character-Song-Album-Slated-for-Release!|title=March Is KonoSuba Month - New Original Soundtrack, Drama CD & Character Song Album Slated for Release!|work=Tokyo Otaku Mode News|date=February 2, 2017|accessdate=August 26, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nThe ''KonoSuba'' light novels have been quite popular. As of March 2, 2016, the 11-volume series has a total of 1.5 million copies in print, each volume selling 136,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2016/03/02/konosuba-novel-sales-increases-three-times-thanks-to-tv-anime|title='KonoSuba' Novel Sales Increases Three Times Thanks to TV Anime|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=March 2, 2016|first=Mikikazu|last=Komatsu}}</ref> As of February 2017, the light novels had three million copies in print.<ref>{{cite web|last=Green|first=Scott|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/02/03/konosuba-art-book-commercial-explodes-online|title=\"Konosuba\" Art Book Commercial Explodes Online|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=February 3, 2017|accessdate=August 26, 2017}}</ref> In a review of the first novel, Andy Hanley praised the series' comedy reflected in the \"tired genre\" as well as its cast finding them appealing based on their traits. However, Hanley criticized the short length of the first volume.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uk-anime.net/manga/Konosuba:_God's_Blessing_on_This_Wonderful_World!_-_Vol._1_(Light_novel).html |title=MANGA REVIEW: Konosuba: God's Blessing on This Wonderful World! - Vol. 1 (Light novel) |last=Hanley |first=Andy|date=February 28, 2017 |website=UK Anime|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref> The series won [[BookWalker]]'s 2016 Grand Prix Award.<ref>{{cite web|last=Komatsu|first=Mikizaku|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/02/03/konosuba-gods-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-wins-book-walker-grand-prix-award-2016|title=\"KONOSUBA -God's blessing on this wonderful world!\" Wins Book Walker Grand Prix Award 2016|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=February 3, 2017|accessdate=September 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\n{{quote box|align=right|width=25em|quote=''KonoSuba: God's Blessing on This Wonderful World'' is an anime that has a lot of fun mocking the tropes of the typical JRPG fantasy world via a colorful cast of characters that are enjoyable in their own right. The comedy is so spot-on with its deadpan nature that it's hard not to be drawn in by that alone.|source=\u2013 Richard Eisenbeis, in his review of the anime<ref name=\"Eisenbeis review\" />}}\n\nLike its light novel counterpart, the anime has received positive reception for its comedy, parody of the isekai genre, and faithful adaptation of the light novels.<ref name=\"Novel vs Anime\" /> Reviewing the first few episodes, [[Anime News Network]] (ANN)'s Theron Martin described the second episode as \"the funniest episode of anime I have seen since ''[[Monthly Girls' Nozaki-kun]]'' aired\", while also praising the series' musical score.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world/episodes-1-2/.97800 |title=KonoSuba \u2013 God's blessing on this wonderful world!! Episodes 1-2 |last=Martin |first=Theron |date=January 21, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802104838/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world/episodes-1-2/.97800|archivedate=August 2, 2017}}</ref> The voice acting has also been a subject of praise; Nick Creamer of ANN commended Sora Amamiya and Rie Takahashi's roles as Aqua and Megumin for the energy provided in their performances,<ref name=\"Creamer review\" /> while Martin applauded Jun Fukushima for his work in voicing Kazuma, considering his dry tone an additional factor in the show's humor.<ref>{{cite web|last=Martin|first=Theron|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-2/episode-7/.112580|title=KONOSUBA - God's blessing on this wonderful world! 2 - Episode 7|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 23, 2017|accessdate=September 1, 2017|quote=Week in and week out, Jun Fukushima knocks it out of the park with his perfectly-measured rendition of Kazuma. In every scene, his inflection and tone is exactly right to milk the maximum value out of a scene's comedy potential. ... The female seiyuu are nailing their roles too, but many scenes in this series wouldn't be half as funny without Kazuma's dry wit as the slightly-less-crazy center of a crazy maelstrom.}}</ref>\n\nFrom the ''Legend of Crimson'''s release in Japan, Daryl Harding, writing for Crunchyroll News praised the story and comedy of the film noting that the \"classic humor of (the TV series) translates well to a film runtime.\" Daryl Harding did criticise the film by stating that \"It doesn\u2019t look too different than the TV series\" even with \"more effects placed over the animation during scenes of explosive magic.\" <ref>{{cite web |last1=Harding |first1=Daryl |url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-feature/2019/09/02/review-konosuba-legend-of-crimson-explodes-into-theaters-but-doesnt-blow-anyone-away | title=REVIEW: Konosuba: Legend of Crimson Explodes Into Theaters But Doesn't Blow Anyone Away |website=Crunchyroll News |publisher=Crunchyroll |accessdate=3 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn contrast, a common criticism of the anime was its inconsistent character animation, one that was described as \"low budget\" as characters appeared [[off-model]].<ref name=\"Novel vs Anime\">{{cite web|last=Morrissy|first=Kim|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-feature/2017/02/27-1/feature-novel-vs-anime-konosuba|title=FEATURE: Novel vs Anime - \"Konosuba\"|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=February 27, 2017|accessdate=August 25, 2017}}</ref> Koichi Kikuta responded by stating such design was intentional, hoping to \"bring out the individuality of each character\" rather than the prettier artwork in the light novels; to do this, Kikuta's animation displayed \"their more human sides, like their unflattering traits and their distressed moments.\"<ref name=\"Interview with Koichi Kikuta\">{{cite web|url=https://wavemotioncannon.com/2017/02/07/konosuba-interview-with-koichi-kikuta-anime-style-009-july-2016/|title=Konosuba Interview with Koichi Kikuta (Anime Style 009, July 2016)|work=Wave Motion Cannon|date=February 7, 2017|accessdate=August 25, 2017}}</ref> [[Crunchyroll]]'s Kim Morrissy considered the animation to be humorous, especially fitting in a comedic anime.<ref name=\"Novel vs Anime\" /> [[Kotaku]] writer Richard Eisenbeis explained much of the series' humor derives from the deconstruction of Kazuma's hopes of becoming the hero of a fantasy world, instead realizing he is forced to struggle his way through the world.<ref name=\"Eisenbeis review\">{{cite web|last=Eisenbeis|first=Richard|url=https://kotaku.com/when-your-new-life-in-a-jrpg-world-doesn-t-live-up-to-e-1778353269|title=When Your New Life in a JRPG World Doesn't Live Up to Expectations|publisher=[[Kotaku]]|date=May 26, 2016|accessdate=August 25, 2017}}</ref> Comparing Kazuma's problems in a fantasy world to those in real life, Creamer wrote about a sense of relatability between the series' protagonists and the audience, as the party deals with issues like debt and taking questionable jobs because of high pay. On a critical note, Creamer disapproved of Kazuma's negative attitude, which he felt harmed the comedy in the series.<ref name=\"Creamer review\">{{cite web|last=Creamer|first=Nick|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-episodes-1-10-streaming/.100209|title=KonoSuba \u2013 God's Blessing on This Wonderful World! [Episodes 1-10 Streaming]|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 25, 2016|accessdate=August 30, 2017}}</ref>\n\n''KonoSuba''{{'s}} characters, especially those in Kazuma's party, have garnered favorable reactions in the anime community. Creamer described the group as possessing a \"strange but endearing chemistry,\" as the members are unfriendly with one another, yet are close.<ref name=\"Creamer review\" /> Morrissy added the party's \"emotional bond is also evident in the ways they interact with each other. My favorite thing about the anime is that it takes the time to draw these nuances out onscreen and express them with visual flair.\"<ref name=\"Novel vs Anime\" /> Megumin in particular has been considered one of the series' most popular characters, winning Sneaker Bunko's official Favorite ''KonoSuba'' Character poll.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sneakerbunko.jp/special/konosuba-charavote/index.php|title=KonoSuba Character Poll|work=[[Kadokawa Sneaker Bunko]]|accessdate=September 1, 2017|language=Japanese}}</ref> She was also the sixth-highest vote in ''[[Newtype]]''{{'s}} 2015\u201316 Awards for Best Female Character (Kazuma was third in the male category) and received the most \"Other\" votes in the Best Girl category in [[Crunchyroll]]'s Anime Awards 2016.<ref name=\"Newtype 2015-16 Awards\">{{cite web|last=Green|first=Scott|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2016/10/09/japanese-fans-pick-favorite-anime-from-last-twelve-months-in-newtype-awards|title=Japanese Fans Pick Favorite Anime From Last Twelve Months In Newtype Awards|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=October 9, 2016|accessdate=September 1, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Crunchyroll Awards 2016\">{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-feature/2017/01/10-1/feature-crunchyroll-anime-awards-the-results-are-in-see-who-won|title=FEATURE: Crunchyroll Anime Awards - The Results are In! See Who Won!|work=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=January 10, 2017|accessdate=September 1, 2017}}</ref> In an interview with internet personality The Anime Man, Natsume Akatsuki described Megumin as giving off \"a pure and elegant atmosphere\" like one of an anime heroine or [[waifu]], hence her popularity among fans.<ref name=\"Akatsuki interview\" />\n\nIn 2016, the anime was voted the tenth-best TV anime in the ''Newtype'' 2015\u201316 Awards.<ref name=\"Newtype 2015-16 Awards\" /> ''KonoSuba'' also finished runner-up for Best Comedy in the Anime Awards 2016 to ''[[Haven't You Heard? I'm Sakamoto]]''.<ref name=\"Crunchyroll Awards 2016\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|KonoSuba}}\n*{{Official website|https://sneakerbunko.jp/series/konosuba/}} {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{Official website|https://konosuba.com/|Official anime website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{Official website|https://www.fujimishobo.co.jp/sp/201504konosuba/|Official manga website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{ann|light novel|18158}}\n\n{{Konosuba}}\n{{Studio Deen}}\n{{J.C.Staff}}\n\n[[Category:2013 Japanese novels]]\n[[Category:2014 Japanese novels]]\n[[Category:2016 anime OVAs]]\n[[Category:2016 Japanese novels]]\n[[Category:2017 video games]]\n[[Category:Anime and manga based on light novels]]\n[[Category:Comedy anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Crunchyroll]]\n[[Category:Fantasy anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Fujimi Shobo manga]]\n[[Category:Isekai anime and manga]]\n[[Category:J.C.Staff]]\n[[Category:Kadokawa Sneaker Bunko]]\n[[Category:Kadokawa Dwango franchises]]\n[[Category:KonoSuba| ]]\n[[Category:Light novels]]\n[[Category:Light novels first published online]]\n[[Category:Media Factory manga]]\n[[Category:Media franchises]]\n[[Category:MMORPGs in fiction]]\n[[Category:Monarchy in fiction]]\n[[Category:Novels about the afterlife]]\n[[Category:Reincarnation in fiction]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Makoto Uezu]]\n[[Category:Sh\u014dsetsuka ni Nar\u014d]]\n[[Category:Studio Deen]]\n[[Category:Sh\u014dnen manga]]\n[[Category:Television programs based on light novels]]\n[[Category:Tokyo MX shows]]\n[[Category:Visual novels]]\n[[Category:Yen Press titles]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World!\n| image           = Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! light novel volume 1 cover.jpg\n| caption         = The first light novel volume cover featuring Kazuma Sat\u014d (left), Megumin and Darkness (above), and Aqua (right).\n| ja_kanji        = \u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092!\n| ja_romaji       = Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o!\n| genre           = [[Comedy]], [[fantasy]], [[isekai]]<ref name=\"Crunchyroll\" /><!-- Note: Use and cite reliable sources to identify genre/s, not personal interpretation. Please don't include more than three genres (per [[MOS:A&M]]). -->\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = novel series\n| title           = \n| author          = Jitakukeibihei (Natsume Akatsuki)\n| illustrator     = \n| publisher       = [[Sh\u014dsetsuka ni Nar\u014d]]\n| first           = December 20, 2012\n| last            = October 21, 2013\n| volumes         = 6\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = light novel\n| author          = Natsume Akatsuki\n| illustrator     = [[Kurone Mishima]]\n| publisher       = [[Kadokawa Shoten]]\n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher|NA=[[Yen Press]]}}\n| demographic     = Male\n| imprint         = [[Kadokawa Sneaker Bunko]]\n| first           = October 1, 2013\n| last            = May 1, 2020\n| volumes         = 17\n| volume_list     = List of KonoSuba volumes#KonoSuba: God's Blessing on This Wonderful World!\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = light novel\n| title           = KonoSuba: An Explosion on this Wonderful World!\n| author          = Natsume Akatsuki\n| illustrator     = Kurone Mishima\n| publisher       = Kadokawa Shoten\n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher|NA=[[Yen Press]]}}\n| demographic     = Male\n| imprint         = Kadokawa Sneaker Bunko\n| first           = July 1, 2014\n| last            = June 1, 2015\n| volumes         = 3\n| volume_list     = List of KonoSuba volumes#Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Bakuen o!\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| author          = Natsume Akatsuki\n| illustrator     = Masahito Watari\n| publisher       = [[Fujimi Shobo]]\n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher|NA=[[Yen Press]]}}\n| demographic     = ''[[Sh\u014dnen manga|Sh\u014dnen]]''\n| magazine        = [[Monthly Dragon Age]]\n| first           = September 9, 2014\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 10\n| volume_list     = List of KonoSuba volumes#Manga\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = tv series\n| director        = Takaomi Kanasaki\n| producer        = Rie Ogura\n| writer          = [[Makoto Uezu]]\n| music           = Masato K\u014dda\n| studio          = [[Studio Deen]]\n| licensee        = {{English anime licensee<!--|AUS=[[Madman Entertainment]]-->|[[British Isles|BI]]/[[North America|NA]]|[[Crunchyroll]]<ref name=\"Crunchyroll License Press Release\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2017-01-24/crunchyroll-announces-winter-2017-anime-lineup/.111421|title=Crunchyroll Announces Winter 2017 Anime Lineup|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=January 20, 2017|accessdate=March 9, 2017}}</ref>}}\n| network         = [[Tokyo MX]], [[TV Saitama]], [[Chiba Television Broadcasting|CTC]], [[Television Kanagawa|tvk]], [[Sun Television|Sun TV]], GBS, MTV, [[TVQ Kyushu Broadcasting|TVQ]], [[Nippon Broadcasting System|BS11]]\n| first           = January 14, 2016\n| last            = March 16, 2017\n| episodes        = 20 + 2 OVAs\n| episode_list    = List of KonoSuba episodes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = light novel\n| title           = Kono Kamen no Akuma ni S\u014ddan o!\n| author          = Natsume Akatsuki\n| illustrator     = Kurone Mishima\n| publisher       = Kadokawa Shoten\n| demographic     = Male\n| imprint         = Kadokawa Sneaker Bunko\n| published       = April 1, 2016\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| title           = Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Bakuen o!\n| author          = Natsume Akatsuki\n| illustrator     = Kasumi Morino\n| publisher       = [[Media Factory]]\n| demographic     = ''[[Sh\u014dnen manga|Sh\u014dnen]]''\n| magazine        = [[Monthly Comic Alive]]\n| first           = May 27, 2016\n| last            = \n| volumes         = \n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = light novel\n| title           = Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! Extra: Ano Orokamono ni mo Kyakkou o!\n| author          = Hirukuma\n| illustrator     = Y\u016bki Hagure\n| publisher       = Kadokawa Shoten\n| demographic     = Male\n| imprint         = Kadokawa Sneaker Bunko\n| first           = August 1, 2017\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 4\n| volume_list     = List of KonoSuba volumes#Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku wo! Extra - Ano Orokamono ni mo Kyakkou wo!\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Game\n| title           = Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! -Kono Yokubukai Game ni Shinpan o!-\n| developer       = [[5pb.]]\n| publisher       = 5pb.<br />[[Ubisoft]]\n| genre           = [[Visual novel]]\n| platforms       = [[PlayStation Vita]], [[PlayStation 4]]\n| released        = September 7, 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gematsu.com/2017/05/konosuba-game-ps4-ps-vita-launches-september-7-japan|title=KonoSuba game for PS4, PS Vita launches September 7 in Japan - Gematsu|author=|date=10 May 2017|website=gematsu.com|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Other\n| title           = Film\n| content         =\n*''[[KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World! Legend of Crimson]]''\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''''KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World!'''''|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092!|Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o!|literally \"A blessing to this wonderful world!\"|lead=yes}}<!--Please do not remove or change the title to its Japanese equivalent without providing the English translation. Wikipedia guidelines dictates we must use the English language title. --> is a Japanese [[light novel]] series written by Natsume Akatsuki. The series follows a boy who is [[isekai|sent to a fantasy world]] following his death, forming a dysfunctional party with a goddess, a wizard, and a crusader to fight against monsters. Beginning as a [[web novel]] series published on [[Sh\u014dsetsuka ni Nar\u014d]] between December 2012 and October 2013, the series was revised into a printed [[light novel]] series with illustrations by Kurone Mishima, which began publication under [[Kadokawa Shoten]]'s ''[[Kadokawa Sneaker Bunko]]'' [[imprint (trade name)|imprint]] from October 2013.\n\nA [[manga]] adaptation, illustrated by Masahito Watari and Joseph Yokobori, began serialization in [[Fujimi Shobo]]'s ''[[Monthly Dragon Age]]'' magazine from October 2014. A radio [[drama CD]] was released by HobiRecords in March 2015, and an [[anime]] television adaptation by [[Studio Deen]] aired in Japan between January and March 2016. A second season of the anime aired between January and March 2017.<ref name=\"S2Anc\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-03-16/konosuba-anime-gets-2nd-season/.99855|title=KonoSuba Anime Gets 2nd Season|date=March 16, 2016|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=March 16, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"s2 Air date\">{{cite web|url=http://nagamedigital.com/2016/11/14/konosuba-season-2-release-date/|title=KONOSUBA SEASON 2 GETS OFFICIAL RELEASE DATE, PV AND KEY VISUAL|date=November 14, 2016|website=nagamedigital.com|accessdate=November 14, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114232041/http://nagamedigital.com/2016/11/14/konosuba-season-2-release-date/|archive-date=November 14, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"s2 January\">{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2016-06-24/konosuba-tv-anime-2nd-season-premieres-in-january/.103579 |title=KonoSuba TV Anime's 2nd Season Premieres in January |date=June 24, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=June 24, 2016 }}</ref> A spin-off light novel series, ''Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Bakuen o!'', began publication from July 2014. Both the light novels and the manga are licensed in North America by [[Yen Press]]. An anime film adaptation by [[J.C.Staff]] titled ''[[KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World! Legend of Crimson]]'' premiered on August 30, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/anime/konosuba-season-3-release-date-new-anime-teased-by-kazuma-megumin-voice-actors-fans-hope-for-bakuen-anime-konosuba-movie-or-ova-3-light-novel-spoilers/|title=KonoSuba Season 3 release date: New anime teased by Kazuma, Megumin voice actors! Fans hope for KonoSuba movie based on Bakuen books, OVA 3 [Light Novel Spoilers]|publisher=[[Monsters and Critics]]|date=October 23, 2018|accessdate=October 23, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n<!-- Note, as the light novel is the PRIMARY work, this plot summary should be written for the light novel, not the anime or manga. -->\n{{See also|List of KonoSuba characters}}\nFollowing an untimely and embarrassing death, Kazuma Sat\u014d, a Japanese teenager [[hikikomori|shut-in]] [[NEET]], meets a goddess named Aqua, who offers to reincarnate him in a [[parallel universe (fiction)|parallel world]] with [[Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|MMORPG]] elements, where he can go on adventures and battle monsters. Despite being offered a superpowered item or ability to use in this new world, Kazuma, following some provocation, chooses Aqua herself to accompany him to the town of Axel, quickly finding her absent-mindedness to be less than beneficial.{{ref|LN|LN 1.P}} With Aqua unable to return to the afterlife until the [[Dark Lord (fiction)|Devil King]] is defeated, the two form a [[Party (role-playing games)|party]] and recruit two other members; an explosion-obsessed magician named Megumin and a masochistic crusader named Darkness.{{ref|LN|LN 1.2.4}} Due to the party's dysfunctional abilities, Kazuma quickly gives up on the idea of defeating the Devil King and tries to live a luxurious lifestyle, only to find the circumstances of his daily life are forcing him and his party to encounter and battle the Devil King's generals.{{ref|LN|LN 2.3}}\n\n==Media==\n===Novels===\n{{See also|List of KonoSuba volumes#Light novels}}\nThe original [[web novel]] series written by Natsume Akatsuki was published on Syosetu between December 2012 and October 2013.<ref name=\"Syosetu\">{{cite web| archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130827082350/http://ncode.syosetu.com/n7145bl/| archivedate=August 27, 2013| url=http://ncode.syosetu.com/n7145bl/| title=KonoSuba web novel| publisher=Syosetu| language=Japanese| accessdate=February 8, 2016}}</ref> The author also wrote a side story featuring Wiz and Vanir.<ref name=\"WN Side\">{{cite web| archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130729143507/http://ncode.syosetu.com/n7364bo/| archivedate=July 29, 2013| url=http://ncode.syosetu.com/n7145bl/| title=The Masked Demon's Dream Watching| publisher=Syosetu| language=Japanese| accessdate=February 8, 2016}}</ref> Akatsuki, who enjoyed playing fantasy video games like ''[[Wizardry]]'' and ''[[Final Fantasy]]'', also derived much of ''KonoSuba''{{'s}} fantasy elements from [[tabletop role-playing game]]s.<ref name=\"Akatsuki interview\">{{cite web|last=Green|first=Scott|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/04/26-1/the-anime-man-interviews-konosuba-creator|title=The Anime Man Interviews \"Konosuba\" Creator|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=April 26, 2017|accessdate=September 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\nA [[light novel]] version with illustrations by Kurone Mishima began release under [[Kadokawa Shoten]]'s [[Kadokawa Sneaker Bunko]] [[Imprint (trade name)|imprint]] from October 1, 2013,<ref name=\"LN1\">{{cite web| url=http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321307000151| script-title=ja:\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01| publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]]| accessdate=May 30, 2015| language=Japanese| title=Archived copy| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150530122639/http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321307000151| archive-date=May 30, 2015| url-status=dead}}</ref> with seventeen volumes released as of May 1, 2020.<ref name=\"LN13\">{{cite web| url=http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321706000257| script-title=ja:\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092!13| publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]]| accessdate=January 20, 2018| language=Japanese| title=Archived copy| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030003500/http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321706000257| archive-date=October 30, 2017| url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"LN16\">{{cite web |title=\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff0116 \u8131\u8d70\u5973\u795e\u3001\u30b4\u30fc\u30db\u30fc\u30e0\uff01 |url=https://sneakerbunko.jp/product/konosuba/321904000247.html |publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]] |accessdate=December 10, 2019 |language=Japanese}}</ref> The light novel diverges significantly from the web novel's plot from the sixth volume onwards,{{citation needed|date=August 2017}} and also features changes to the characters' ages. The final book in the series, Volume 17, contains an After Story in the Afterward section that extends the ending of the original web novel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/anime/konosuba-ending-light-novel-volume-17-after-story-natsume-akatsuki-konosuba-gods-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-books/|title=KonoSuba ending with light novel Volume 17: After story to finish Natsume Akatsuki\u2019s KonoSuba: God\u2019s Blessing on this Wonderful World! books|publisher=[[Monsters and Critics]]|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\nA Megumin-focused [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] light novel series, also written and illustrated by Akatsuki and Mishima respectively, titled {{nihongo3|lit. \"Give Explosions to This Wonderful World!\"|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u7206\u7114\u3092\uff01|Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Bakuen o!}} and takes place a year prior to the main series, began release from July 1, 2014, with three volumes released as of June 1, 2015.<ref name=\"MegLN1\">{{cite web|url=http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321403000163|script-title=ja:\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u7206\u7114\u3092\uff01|publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]]|accessdate=June 6, 2015|language=Japanese|title=Archived copy|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150319035638/http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321403000163|archive-date=March 19, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> A sequel novel was released December 28, 2016,<ref name=\"MegSequelLN1\">{{cite web |url=http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321607000363 |script-title=ja:\u7d9a\u30fb\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u7206\u7114\u3092\uff01 |publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]] |accessdate=February 11, 2017 |language=Japanese |title=Archived copy |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180118182424/http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321607000363 |archive-date=January 18, 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref> named {{nihongo3|lit. \"Sequel: Give Explosions to This Wonderful World!\"|\u7d9a\u30fb\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u7206\u7114\u3092\uff01|Zoku: Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Bakuen o!}}. Another spin-off featuring Vanir was published on April 1, 2016, called {{nihongo3|lit. \"Consulting with the Masked Devil!\"|\u3053\u306e\u4eee\u9762\u306e\u60aa\u9b54\u306b\u76f8\u8ac7\u3092\uff01|Kono Kamen no Akuma ni S\u014ddan o!}}.<ref name=\"VanLN1\">{{cite web|url=http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321601000557|script-title=ja:\u3053\u306e\u4eee\u9762\u306e\u60aa\u9b54\u306b\u76f8\u8ac7\u3092\uff01|publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]]|accessdate=June 30, 2016|language=Japanese|title=Archived copy|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160402060707/http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321601000557|archive-date=April 2, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nA third spin-off series titled {{nihongo3|lit. \"Bless Me in This Wonderful World! Extra: Attention Also to That Fool!\"|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u30a8\u30af\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9 \u3042\u306e\u611a\u304b\u8005\u306b\u3082\u811a\u5149\u3092\uff01|Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! Extra Ano Orokamono ni mo Kyakkou o!}} began publication on August 1, 2017. It is written by Hirukuma and illustrated by Uihime Hagure, and features Dust as the central character.<ref name=\"ExLN1\">{{cite web|url=http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321703000426|title=\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u30a8\u30af\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9 \u3042\u306e\u611a\u304b\u8005\u306b\u3082\u811a\u5149\u3092\uff01|publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]]|accessdate=January 29, 2018|language=Japanese|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030003504/http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321703000426|archive-date=October 30, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> The second volume was released on December 1, 2017.<ref name=\"ExLN2\">{{cite web|url=http://sneakerbunko.jp/bookdetails/index.php?pcd=321703000427|title=\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u30a8\u30af\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9 \u3042\u306e\u611a\u304b\u8005\u306b\u3082\u811a\u5149\u3092\uff012|publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]]|accessdate=January 29, 2018|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n[[Yen Press]] announced on May 20, 2016 that it had licensed the light novels for release in North America.<ref name=\"Yen Press\">{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-05-20/yen-press-licenses-konosuba-death-march-to-the-parallel-world-rhapsody-manga-light-novels/.102332 |title=Yen Press Licenses Konosuba, Death March to the Parallel World Rhapsody Manga, Light Novels |date=May 20, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=May 20, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170702032320/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-05-20/yen-press-licenses-konosuba-death-march-to-the-parallel-world-rhapsody-manga-light-novels/.102332|archivedate=July 2, 2017}}</ref> The first volume was released in conjunction with the second manga volume on February 21, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://yenpress.com/2017/02/konosuba-gods-blessing-on-this-hilariously-frustrating-world/|title=Konosuba: God's Blessing on This Hilariously Frustrating World|work=[[Yen Press]]|date=February 21, 2017|accessdate=August 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Manga===\n{{See also|List of KonoSuba volumes#Manga}}\nA [[manga]] adaption of ''KonoSuba'' illustrated by Masahito Watari began serialization in the October 2014 issue of [[Fujimi Shobo]]'s ''[[Monthly Dragon Age]]'' magazine on September 9, 2014.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://natalie.mu/comic/news/125663| title=''Omamori Himari'', Milan Matra's New Series| publisher=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]| date=September 9, 2014| accessdate=October 30, 2015| language=Japanese}}</ref> Eight ''tank\u014dbon'' volumes have been released as of May 2019. A spin-off manga, ''A Spotlight For (Even) This fool! Gifting this Wonderful World with Blessings! Extra'', was released as a bundle with the twelfth light novel volume. Written and illustrated by Kuma Hiru and Hagure Yuki, respectively, it follows the story of Dust, who finds himself in trouble with Vanir over selling stolen products.<ref>{{cite web|last=Green|first=Scott|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/06/16/konosuba-anticipates-humiliation-a-new-ova-and-cover-previews|title=\"Konosuba\" Anticipates Humiliation, a New OVA and Cover Previews|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=June 16, 2017|accessdate=September 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\nYen Press announced its acquisition of the manga adaptation at the same time that it licensed the original light novels.<ref name=\"Yen Press\"/>\n\n===Anime===\n{{See also|List of KonoSuba episodes}}\nAn [[anime]] television adaptation by [[Studio Deen]]<ref name=\"AnimeAnnouncement\">{{cite web| url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-05-25/kono-subarashii-sekai-ni-shukufuku-o-alternate-world-comedy-light-novels-get-tv-anime/.88540| title=''KonoSuba'' TV Anime Announcement| publisher=[[Anime News Network]]| date=May 25, 2015| accessdate=May 25, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170626203637/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-05-25/kono-subarashii-sekai-ni-shukufuku-o-alternate-world-comedy-light-novels-get-tv-anime/.88540|archivedate=June 26, 2017}}</ref> aired on [[Tokyo MX]] between January 14, 2016, and March 16, 2016;<ref name=\"Networks\">{{cite web| url=http://konosuba.com/1st/onair/| title=''KonoSuba'' Network Information|  publisher=KonoSuba.com| language=Japanese| accessdate=January 29, 2016|quote=TOKYO MX &ndash; 1\u670813\u65e5\u3088\u308a\u6bce\u9031\u6c34\u66dc &ndash; 25:05 \uff5e 25:35}}</ref> later broadcasting on eight other networks and several [[video on demand]] [[streaming media|streaming networks]].<ref name=\"Networks\"/> The series was simulcast by [[Crunchyroll]] in several regions such as North America,<ref name=\"Crunchyroll\">{{cite web| url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-01-12/crunchyroll-to-stream-konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-anime/.97499| title=Crunchyroll to Stream KonoSuba| date=January 12, 2016| publisher=[[Anime News Network]]| accessdate=February 1, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170728231301/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-01-12/crunchyroll-to-stream-konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-anime/.97499|archivedate=July 28, 2017}}</ref> and by [[AnimeLab]] in Australia.<ref name=\"AnimeLab\">{{cite web| url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-22/new-titles-for-animelab-2016-winter-simulcast-season/.96781| title=New Titles for AnimeLab 2016 Winter Simulcast Season| date=December 21, 2015| publisher=[[Anime News Network]]| accessdate=February 8, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170729011400/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-22/new-titles-for-animelab-2016-winter-simulcast-season/.96781|archivedate=July 29, 2017}}</ref>  The series was directed by Takaomi Kanasaki and written by [[Makoto Uezu]] with character designs by Koichi Kikuta.<ref name=\"AnimeAnnouncement\" /> An [[original video animation]] (OVA) was bundled with the ninth light novel of ''KonoSuba'' in June 2016.<ref name=\"OVA1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-21/kono-subarashii-sekai-ni-shukufuku-o-light-novel-bundles-original-anime-blu-ray/.96791| title=''KonoSuba'' Light Novel Bundles Original Anime Blu-ray| publisher=[[Anime News Network]]| date=December 21, 2015| accessdate=December 21, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170726160432/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-21/kono-subarashii-sekai-ni-shukufuku-o-light-novel-bundles-original-anime-blu-ray/.96791|archivedate=July 26, 2017}}</ref> The anime's opening theme is \"Fantastic Dreamer\" by [[Machico (singer)|Machico]] while the ending theme is {{nihongo|\"Ch\u012bsana B\u014dken-sha\"|\u3061\u3044\u3055\u306a\u5192\u967a\u8005|lit.\"Little Adventurer\"}} performed by [[Sora Amamiya]], [[Rie Takahashi]], and [[Ai Kayano]].<ref name=\"Staff\">{{cite web| url=http://konosuba.com/1st/staff_cast/| title=KonoSuba anime staff| publisher=KonoSuba.com| language=Japanese| accessdate=January 31, 2016}}</ref> On January 7, 2019, Crunchyroll announced that the series would receive an English dub.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-01-07/crunchyroll-to-stream-konosuba-anime-dubbed-in-english-spanish-portuguese/.141729|last=Ressler|first=Karen|title=Crunchyroll to Stream Konosuba Anime Dubbed in English, Spanish, Portuguese|date=January 7, 2019|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]| accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref> The season 1 dub made its debut on January 25, 2019,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/konosuba-finally-has-an-english-dub-and-heres-wher/1100-6464212/|title=Konosuba Finally Has An English Dub, And Here's Where You Can Watch It|website=GameSpot|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-07}}</ref> with the second season's dub being released on February 25, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|last=Luster|first=Joseph|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2020/02/15-1/konosuba-season-2-dub-comes-to-crunchyroll-on-february-25|title=KONOSUBA Season 2 Dub Comes to Crunchyroll on February 25|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=February 15, 2020|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref> [[Discotek Media]] will release the first season on Blu-ray in North America, with the release scheduled for May 25, 2020.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=discotekmedia|author=Discotek Media|author-link=Discotek Media|number=1237437365527949312|date=March 10, 2020|title=Today, we woke up to the amazing and wonderful news that WE, Discotek Media, are releasing Konosuba: God's Blessing On this Wonderful World season 1 on Blu-Ray this May!! The OVA is included, too!!! https://rightstufanime.com/Konosuba-Season-1-OVA-Blu-ray|accessdate=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe series was animated by Koichi Kikuta and Momoka Komatsu, with the former working on odd-numbered episodes and the latter on even-numbered. While Komatsu's character designs closely resembled those of the light novels and had more attractive appearances, Kikuta based his designs on children's shows like ''[[Pok\u00e9mon (anime)|Pok\u00e9mon]]'' as he felt ''KonoSuba''{{'s}} story was similar to those found in such shows.<ref name=\"Interview with Koichi Kikuta\" />\n\nA second season aired between January 12, 2017, and March 16, 2017.<ref name=\"S2Anc\"/><ref name=\"s2 Air date\"/><ref name=\"s2 January\" /> The second season's opening theme is \"Tomorrow\" by Machico, and the ending theme is {{nihongo|\"Ouchi ni Kaeritai\"|\u304a\u5bb6\u306b\u5e30\u308a\u305f\u3044|lit.\"Want to Go Home\"}} by Amamiya, Takahashi, and Kayano.<ref>{{cite web|title=KonoSuba 2 Anime's Promo Video Previews Machico's Opening Theme|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-12-12/konosuba-2-anime-promo-video-previews-machico-opening-theme/.109782|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=December 13, 2016|date=December 12, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731160957/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-12-12/konosuba-2-anime-promo-video-previews-machico-opening-theme/.109782|archivedate=July 31, 2017}}</ref> A second OVA was bundled with the twelfth volume of ''KonoSuba'' in July 2017.<ref name=\"OVA2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-12-26/konosuba-light-novel-to-bundle-original-anime-blu-ray/.110350|title=KonoSuba Light Novel to Bundle Original Anime Blu-ray|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 26, 2016|accessdate=December 26, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731004431/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-12-26/konosuba-light-novel-to-bundle-original-anime-blu-ray/.110350|archivedate=July 31, 2017}}</ref> On July 25, 2017, [[Jun Fukushima]] and Takahashi, the voice actors of Kazuma and Megumin respectively, announced plans for a new ''KonoSuba'' anime project, later revealed to be a new movie, [[KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World! Legend of Crimson]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-07-25/konosuba-comedy-fantasy-anime-gets-new-anime-project/.119285 |title=KonoSuba Comedy Fantasy Anime Gets New Anime Project |date=July 25, 2017 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=January 20, 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Green|first=Scott|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/07/25-1/new-konosuba-anime-project-announced|title=New \"Konosuba\" Anime Project Announced|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=July 25, 2017|accessdate=August 26, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn October 6, 2018, it was announced that characters from ''KonoSuba'' would appear in ''[[Isekai Quartet]]'', a crossover anime also featuring characters from ''[[Re:Zero \u2212 Starting Life in Another World]]'', ''[[Overlord (novel series)|Overlord]]'', and ''[[The Saga of Tanya the Evil]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-10-06/new-isekai-quartet-anime-project-crosses-over-overlord-re-zero-tanya-konosuba-franchises/.137803 |title=New Isekai Quartet Anime Project Crosses Over Overlord, Re:Zero, Tanya, Konosuba Franchises |date=October 6, 2018 |website=Anime News Network |accessdate=October 14, 2018 }}</ref>\n\n===Film===\n{{see also|KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World! Legend of Crimson}}\nOn June 25, 2018, a film adaptation was announced to be in development at [[J.C.Staff]]. The cast and staff reprised their roles from the TV series.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hodgkins |first1=Crystalyn |title=Konosuba - God's Blessing on This Wonderful World! Anime Gets Film Project |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-06-25/konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-anime-gets-film-project/.133376 |website=Anime News Network |accessdate=June 25, 2018 |date=June 25, 2018}}</ref> The film is titled {{nihongo|''KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World! Crimson Legend''|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u7d05\u4f1d\u8aac|Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! Kurenai Densetsu}},<ref>{{cite web |title=\u300e\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u7d05\u4f1d\u8aac\u300f\u30c6\u30a3\u30b6\u30fc\u30d3\u30b8\u30e5\u30a2\u30eb\u516c\u958b\uff01 |url=https://konosuba.com/2nd/news/?mode=detail&id=20181104_1 |publisher=[[Kadokawa Corporation]] |accessdate=November 5, 2018 |language=Japanese |date=November 5, 2018}}</ref> and it premiered in Japan on August 30, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hodgkins |first1=Crystalyn|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2018-10-20/konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-anime-film-opens-in-2019/.138430|title=KONOSUBA - God's blessing on this wonderful world! Anime Film Opens in 2019|date=October 20, 2018|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=October 20, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Pineda |first1=Rafael Antonio|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-04-25/konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-anime-film-reveals-song-artists-august-debut/.146140|title=KONOSUBA - God's blessing on this wonderful world! Anime Film Reveals Song Artists, August Debut|date=April 25, 2019|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=April 25, 2019}}</ref> Crunchyroll began streaming the English subtitles and English dub version in March and April of 2020, respectively.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Frye|first1=Patrick |title=Crunchyroll streaming KonoSuba: Legend of Crimson English dub/sub for movie release in 2020 |url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/anime/crunchyroll-streaming-konosuba-legend-of-crimson-english-dub-sub-movie-release-date-2020/ |website=[[Monsters and Critics]] |accessdate=March 10, 2020 |date=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Video games===\nA PC [[video game]] developed by game creator Tachi, titled {{nihongo|''Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! In The Life''|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01in the life}}, is bundled with the first Blu-ray Disc/DVD volume of the anime series on March 25, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-02-13/konosuba-1st-blu-ray-dvd-to-include-pc-game/.98637 |title=KonoSuba's 1st Blu-ray/DVD to Include PC Game |date=February 13, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802002325/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-02-13/konosuba-1st-blu-ray-dvd-to-include-pc-game/.98637|archivedate=August 2, 2017}}</ref> The game is developed using the software [[RPG Maker VX]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Blu-ray\u9650\u5b9a\u7248&DVD\u9650\u5b9a\u7248\u3000\u7b2c1\u5dfb\u3000\u8d85\u8c6a\u83ef5\u5927\u7279\u5178\uff01\uff01|url=http://konosuba.com/1st/bd/?mode=detail&id=bd1|website=\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u300e\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u300f\u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=August 21, 2016|language=Japanese}}</ref> Another video game, created by Team Ladybug and Krobon, titled ''KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World! Revival of Beldia'' ({{nihongo|''Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! Fukatsu no Verdier''|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u5fa9\u6d3b\u306e\u30d9\u30eb\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2}}) is bundled with the limited edition of first Blu-ray Disc/DVD volume of the anime series' second season and was released on April 28, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u300c\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\uff12\u300d Blu-ray & DVD \u7b2c1\u5dfb|url=http://konosuba.com/bd/?mode=detail&id=bd1|website=\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u300e\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff012\u300f\u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8|accessdate=March 30, 2017|language=Japanese}}</ref> The game is a [[side-scrolling video game|side-scroller]] with gameplay resembling the ''[[Mega Man (video game)|Mega Man]]'' series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/2017/02/01/konosubas-season-2-limited-blu-ray-bonus-sweet-mega-man-style-side-scroller/|title=KonoSuba's Season 2 Limited Blu-ray Bonus Is A Sweet Mega Man-Style Side-Scroller|publisher=Siliconera|date=February 1, 2017|accessdate=August 25, 2017}}</ref>\n\nA visual novel adaptation for [[PlayStation Vita]] and [[PlayStation 4]], ''KonoSuba: God's Blessing on this Wonderful World! Judgment on this Greedy Game!'' ({{nihongo|''Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! -Kono Yokubukai Game ni Shinpan o!-''|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01 -\u3053\u306e\u6b32\u6df1\u3044\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u306b\u5be9\u5224\u3092\uff01-}}), was developed by [[5pb.]], published by [[Ubisoft]] and was released in Japan on September 7, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/2017/05/10/konosubas-new-game-releases-september-7-japan-comes-bonus-konosuba-shooting-game/v|title=KonoSuba's New Game Releases September 7 In Japan, Comes With Bonus KonoSuba Shooting Game|work=Siliconera|date=May 10, 2017|accessdate=August 26, 2017}}</ref> The game features an original story, in which Kazuma discovers a cursed ring that allows him to steal the underwear of others near him. He learns the only way to undo the curse would be through raising enough money. ''Judgment on this Greedy Game!'' introduces an \"Underwear Judgment\" system, where the player assists Kazuma in returning lost underwear to their rightful owner.<ref>{{cite web|last=Romano|first=Sal|title=KonoSuba game launches for PS4 and PS Vita this summer in Japan|url=https://gematsu.com/2017/03/konosuba-game-launches-ps4-ps-vita-summer-japan|publisher=Gematsu|accessdate=March 30, 2017}}</ref> Like the anime, Machico performed the opening \"Million Smile\", while Amamiya, Takahashi, and Kayano sang the game's ending theme \"101 Pikime no Hitsuji\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Green|first=Scott|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/07/23/hear-cast-and-machico-sing-konosuba-game-themes|title=Hear Cast And Machico Sing \"Konosuba\" Game Themes|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=July 23, 2017|accessdate=August 26, 2017}}</ref>\n\nA mobile game titled {{nihongo|''Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku o! Fantastic Days''|\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u30d5\u30a1\u30f3\u30bf\u30b9\u30c6\u30a3\u30c3\u30af\u30c7\u30a4\u30ba}} was released for iOS and Android devices on February 27, 2020.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u3010\u516c\u5f0f\u3011\u300a\u597d\u8a55\u914d\u4fe1\u4e2d\u300b\u3053\u306e\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u795d\u798f\u3092\uff01\u30d5\u30a1\u30f3\u30bf\u30b9\u30c6\u30a3\u30c3\u30af\u30c7\u30a4\u30ba\uff08\u3053\u306e\u30d5\u30a1\u30f3\uff09 |url=https://konosubafd.jp/ |accessdate=March 25, 2020 |language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n===Audio CDs===\nA radio [[drama CD]], featuring a different voice cast to the anime, was released by HobiRecords on March 1, 2015.<ref name=\"Drama CD\">{{cite web| url=https://www.toranoana.jp/info/dojin/konosuba/| title=KonoSuba Drama CD| publisher=[[Comic Toranoana]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=January 29, 2016}}</ref> A second drama CD, along with an original soundtrack by Kouda Masato and a [[character song]] album, was released in March 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://otakumode.com/news/5891ab30e088942e19129b4f/March-Is-KonoSuba-Month-New-Original-Soundtrack-Drama-CD-Character-Song-Album-Slated-for-Release!|title=March Is KonoSuba Month - New Original Soundtrack, Drama CD & Character Song Album Slated for Release!|work=Tokyo Otaku Mode News|date=February 2, 2017|accessdate=August 26, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nThe ''KonoSuba'' light novels have been quite popular. As of March 2, 2016, the 11-volume series has a total of 1.5 million copies in print, each volume selling 136,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2016/03/02/konosuba-novel-sales-increases-three-times-thanks-to-tv-anime|title='KonoSuba' Novel Sales Increases Three Times Thanks to TV Anime|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=March 2, 2016|first=Mikikazu|last=Komatsu}}</ref> As of February 2017, the light novels had three million copies in print.<ref>{{cite web|last=Green|first=Scott|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/02/03/konosuba-art-book-commercial-explodes-online|title=\"Konosuba\" Art Book Commercial Explodes Online|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=February 3, 2017|accessdate=August 26, 2017}}</ref> In a review of the first novel, Andy Hanley praised the series' comedy reflected in the \"tired genre\" as well as its cast finding them appealing based on their traits. However, Hanley criticized the short length of the first volume.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uk-anime.net/manga/Konosuba:_God's_Blessing_on_This_Wonderful_World!_-_Vol._1_(Light_novel).html |title=MANGA REVIEW: Konosuba: God's Blessing on This Wonderful World! - Vol. 1 (Light novel) |last=Hanley |first=Andy|date=February 28, 2017 |website=UK Anime|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref> The series won [[BookWalker]]'s 2016 Grand Prix Award.<ref>{{cite web|last=Komatsu|first=Mikizaku|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/02/03/konosuba-gods-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-wins-book-walker-grand-prix-award-2016|title=\"KONOSUBA -God's blessing on this wonderful world!\" Wins Book Walker Grand Prix Award 2016|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=February 3, 2017|accessdate=September 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\n{{quote box|align=right|width=25em|quote=''KonoSuba: God's Blessing on This Wonderful World'' is an anime that has a lot of fun mocking the tropes of the typical JRPG fantasy world via a colorful cast of characters that are enjoyable in their own right. The comedy is so spot-on with its deadpan nature that it's hard not to be drawn in by that alone.|source=\u2013 Richard Eisenbeis, in his review of the anime<ref name=\"Eisenbeis review\" />}}\n\nLike its light novel counterpart, the anime has received positive reception for its comedy, parody of the isekai genre, and faithful adaptation of the light novels.<ref name=\"Novel vs Anime\" /> Reviewing the first few episodes, [[Anime News Network]] (ANN)'s Theron Martin described the second episode as \"the funniest episode of anime I have seen since ''[[Monthly Girls' Nozaki-kun]]'' aired\", while also praising the series' musical score.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world/episodes-1-2/.97800 |title=KonoSuba \u2013 God's blessing on this wonderful world!! Episodes 1-2 |last=Martin |first=Theron |date=January 21, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802104838/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world/episodes-1-2/.97800|archivedate=August 2, 2017}}</ref> The voice acting has also been a subject of praise; Nick Creamer of ANN commended Sora Amamiya and Rie Takahashi's roles as Aqua and Megumin for the energy provided in their performances,<ref name=\"Creamer review\" /> while Martin applauded Jun Fukushima for his work in voicing Kazuma, considering his dry tone an additional factor in the show's humor.<ref>{{cite web|last=Martin|first=Theron|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-2/episode-7/.112580|title=KONOSUBA - God's blessing on this wonderful world! 2 - Episode 7|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 23, 2017|accessdate=September 1, 2017|quote=Week in and week out, Jun Fukushima knocks it out of the park with his perfectly-measured rendition of Kazuma. In every scene, his inflection and tone is exactly right to milk the maximum value out of a scene's comedy potential. ... The female seiyuu are nailing their roles too, but many scenes in this series wouldn't be half as funny without Kazuma's dry wit as the slightly-less-crazy center of a crazy maelstrom.}}</ref>\n\nFrom the ''Legend of Crimson'''s release in Japan, Daryl Harding, writing for Crunchyroll News praised the story and comedy of the film noting that the \"classic humor of (the TV series) translates well to a film runtime.\" Daryl Harding did criticise the film by stating that \"It doesn\u2019t look too different than the TV series\" even with \"more effects placed over the animation during scenes of explosive magic.\" <ref>{{cite web |last1=Harding |first1=Daryl |url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-feature/2019/09/02/review-konosuba-legend-of-crimson-explodes-into-theaters-but-doesnt-blow-anyone-away | title=REVIEW: Konosuba: Legend of Crimson Explodes Into Theaters But Doesn't Blow Anyone Away |website=Crunchyroll News |publisher=Crunchyroll |accessdate=3 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn contrast, a common criticism of the anime was its inconsistent character animation, one that was described as \"low budget\" as characters appeared [[off-model]].<ref name=\"Novel vs Anime\">{{cite web|last=Morrissy|first=Kim|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-feature/2017/02/27-1/feature-novel-vs-anime-konosuba|title=FEATURE: Novel vs Anime - \"Konosuba\"|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=February 27, 2017|accessdate=August 25, 2017}}</ref> Koichi Kikuta responded by stating such design was intentional, hoping to \"bring out the individuality of each character\" rather than the prettier artwork in the light novels; to do this, Kikuta's animation displayed \"their more human sides, like their unflattering traits and their distressed moments.\"<ref name=\"Interview with Koichi Kikuta\">{{cite web|url=https://wavemotioncannon.com/2017/02/07/konosuba-interview-with-koichi-kikuta-anime-style-009-july-2016/|title=Konosuba Interview with Koichi Kikuta (Anime Style 009, July 2016)|work=Wave Motion Cannon|date=February 7, 2017|accessdate=August 25, 2017}}</ref> [[Crunchyroll]]'s Kim Morrissy considered the animation to be humorous, especially fitting in a comedic anime.<ref name=\"Novel vs Anime\" /> [[Kotaku]] writer Richard Eisenbeis explained much of the series' humor derives from the deconstruction of Kazuma's hopes of becoming the hero of a fantasy world, instead realizing he is forced to struggle his way through the world.<ref name=\"Eisenbeis review\">{{cite web|last=Eisenbeis|first=Richard|url=https://kotaku.com/when-your-new-life-in-a-jrpg-world-doesn-t-live-up-to-e-1778353269|title=When Your New Life in a JRPG World Doesn't Live Up to Expectations|publisher=[[Kotaku]]|date=May 26, 2016|accessdate=August 25, 2017}}</ref> Comparing Kazuma's problems in a fantasy world to those in real life, Creamer wrote about a sense of relatability between the series' protagonists and the audience, as the party deals with issues like debt and taking questionable jobs because of high pay. On a critical note, Creamer disapproved of Kazuma's negative attitude, which he felt harmed the comedy in the series.<ref name=\"Creamer review\">{{cite web|last=Creamer|first=Nick|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/konosuba-god-blessing-on-this-wonderful-world-episodes-1-10-streaming/.100209|title=KonoSuba \u2013 God's Blessing on This Wonderful World! [Episodes 1-10 Streaming]|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 25, 2016|accessdate=August 30, 2017}}</ref>\n\n''KonoSuba''{{'s}} characters, especially those in Kazuma's party, have garnered favorable reactions in the anime community. Creamer described the group as possessing a \"strange but endearing chemistry,\" as the members are unfriendly with one another, yet are close.<ref name=\"Creamer review\" /> Morrissy added the party's \"emotional bond is also evident in the ways they interact with each other. My favorite thing about the anime is that it takes the time to draw these nuances out onscreen and express them with visual flair.\"<ref name=\"Novel vs Anime\" /> Megumin in particular has been considered one of the series' most popular characters, winning Sneaker Bunko's official Favorite ''KonoSuba'' Character poll.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sneakerbunko.jp/special/konosuba-charavote/index.php|title=KonoSuba Character Poll|work=[[Kadokawa Sneaker Bunko]]|accessdate=September 1, 2017|language=Japanese}}</ref> She was also the sixth-highest vote in ''[[Newtype]]''{{'s}} 2015\u201316 Awards for Best Female Character (Kazuma was third in the male category) and received the most \"Other\" votes in the Best Girl category in [[Crunchyroll]]'s Anime Awards 2016.<ref name=\"Newtype 2015-16 Awards\">{{cite web|last=Green|first=Scott|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2016/10/09/japanese-fans-pick-favorite-anime-from-last-twelve-months-in-newtype-awards|title=Japanese Fans Pick Favorite Anime From Last Twelve Months In Newtype Awards|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=October 9, 2016|accessdate=September 1, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Crunchyroll Awards 2016\">{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-feature/2017/01/10-1/feature-crunchyroll-anime-awards-the-results-are-in-see-who-won|title=FEATURE: Crunchyroll Anime Awards - The Results are In! See Who Won!|work=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=January 10, 2017|accessdate=September 1, 2017}}</ref> In an interview with internet personality The Anime Man, Natsume Akatsuki described Megumin as giving off \"a pure and elegant atmosphere\" like one of an anime heroine or [[waifu]], hence her popularity among fans.<ref name=\"Akatsuki interview\" />\n\nIn 2016, the anime was voted the tenth-best TV anime in the ''Newtype'' 2015\u201316 Awards.<ref name=\"Newtype 2015-16 Awards\" /> ''KonoSuba'' also finished runner-up for Best Comedy in the Anime Awards 2016 to ''[[Haven't You Heard? I'm Sakamoto]]''.<ref name=\"Crunchyroll Awards 2016\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|KonoSuba}}\n*{{Official website|https://sneakerbunko.jp/series/konosuba/}} {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{Official website|https://konosuba.com/|Official anime website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{Official website|https://www.fujimishobo.co.jp/sp/201504konosuba/|Official manga website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{ann|light novel|18158}}\n\n{{Konosuba}}\n{{Studio Deen}}\n{{J.C.Staff}}\n\n[[Category:2013 Japanese novels]]\n[[Category:2014 Japanese novels]]\n[[Category:2016 anime OVAs]]\n[[Category:2016 Japanese novels]]\n[[Category:2017 video games]]\n[[Category:Anime and manga based on light novels]]\n[[Category:Comedy anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Crunchyroll]]\n[[Category:Fantasy anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Fujimi Shobo manga]]\n[[Category:Isekai anime and manga]]\n[[Category:J.C.Staff]]\n[[Category:Kadokawa Sneaker Bunko]]\n[[Category:Kadokawa Dwango franchises]]\n[[Category:KonoSuba| ]]\n[[Category:Light novels]]\n[[Category:Light novels first published online]]\n[[Category:Media Factory manga]]\n[[Category:Media franchises]]\n[[Category:MMORPGs in fiction]]\n[[Category:Monarchy in fiction]]\n[[Category:Novels about the afterlife]]\n[[Category:Reincarnation in fiction]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Makoto Uezu]]\n[[Category:Sh\u014dsetsuka ni Nar\u014d]]\n[[Category:Studio Deen]]\n[[Category:Sh\u014dnen manga]]\n[[Category:Television programs based on light novels]]\n[[Category:Tokyo MX shows]]\n[[Category:Visual novels]]\n[[Category:Yen Press titles]]\n", "name_user": "Narutolovehinata5", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAnime:italics", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KonoSuba"}
{"title_page": "An Qi", "text_new": "{{short description|Chinese footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| image =\n| name                = An Qi<br />\u5b89\u7426\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1981|6|21}}\n| birth_place = [[Dalian]], [[Liaoning]], [[People's Republic of China|China]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.91}}\n| position            = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| youthyears1 = 1997\u20131998\n| youthclubs1 = [[Harbin Yiteng|Dalian Yiteng]]\n| years1 = 1999\u20132000 \n| years2 = 2000\u20132004 \n| years3 = 2004\u20132005 \n| years4 = 2006\u20132007 \n| years5 = 2008\u20132010\n| clubs1 = [[Guangzhou Songri]] \n| clubs2 = [[Dalian Shide]] \n| clubs3 = [[Dalian Changbo]] \n| clubs4 = [[Xiamen Lanshi]] \n| clubs5 = [[Changchun Yatai]]\n| caps1 = 2  \n| caps2 = 68  \n| caps3 = 15  \n| caps4 = 43  \n| caps5 = 1  \n| goals1 = 0  \n| goals2 = 0  \n| goals3 = 2  \n| goals4 = 0  \n| goals5 = 0 \n| totalcaps = 129 \n| totalgoals = 2\n| nationalyears1 = 2001\n| nationalteam1 = [[China national under-20 football team|China U20]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 4  \n| nationalgoals1 = 0 \n| nationalyears2 = 2001\u20132004\n| nationalteam2 = [[China national football team|China]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 9  \n| nationalgoals2 = 0 \n| pcupdate            = 6 March 2013\n| ntupdate            = 6 March 2013\n}}\n\n{{Chinese name|[[An (surname)|An]]}}\n{{about|the football player|the Chinese female poet|An Qi (poet)}}\n\n'''An Qi''' ({{zh|c=\u5b89\u7426|p=\u0100n Q\u00ed}}) (born 21 June 1981 in [[Dalian]], [[Liaoning]], [[People's Republic of China|China]]) is a former [[Chinese people|Chinese]] international association football goalkeeper. He represented [[Guangzhou Songri]], [[Dalian Shide]], [[Dalian Changbo]], [[Xiamen Lanshi]] and [[Changchun Yatai]] while internationally he participated for the [[China national football team|Chinese national team]] that took part in the [[2002 FIFA World Cup]], however he did not feature in any of the games.\n\n==Club career==\nAn Qi originally started his senior career with [[Guangzhou Songri]] before he was called up to the [[China national under-20 football team|Chinese U20 team]] that took part in the [[2001 FIFA World Youth Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=181025/index.html |title=An Qi |publisher=fifa.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref> After the tournament he was considered one of the most promising young goalkeepers within China and had already drawn the interests of reigning Chinese league champions [[Dalian Shide]] where he established himself as their first-choice goalkeeper within the 2002 league season, in time to also be called up to the [[China national football team|Chinese football team]] for the 2002 FIFA World Cup.<ref name=\"WC profile\">{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport3/worldcup2002/hi/team_pages/china/squad/newsid_1950000/1950527.stm|title=BBC World Cup profile|publisher=bbc.co.uk|date=20 May 2002|accessdate=2010-12-22}}</ref> After several seasons with Dalian Shide, An Qi's position would come into question when on April 9, 2003 the club lost 4-2 to [[Al Ain FC]] in a [[2002\u201303 AFC Champions League]] semi-final match, which saw An Qi have a personally disappointing game.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesa/ascup03.html#cl |title=Asian Club Competitions 2002/03 |publisher=rsssf.com |date= 12 Dec 2003 |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref> Throughout the rest of the campaign he would have to fight for his position against [[Song Zhenyu]] until the club brought in [[Vladimir Petrovi\u0107]] as their new manager who decided to drop An Qi from the squad.\n\nAn Qi went on loan to second-tier side [[Dalian Changbo]] to help revive his career at the beginning of the 2005 league season, however he had a disastrous competitive debut when his club lost 9-0 to [[Changchun Yatai]] on March 5, 2005, in the team's opening league game of the campaign.<ref name=\"China 2005\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesc/china05.html|title=China 2005|publisher=rsssf.com |date=26 Oct 2006|accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref> Despite his disappointing start with his new club An Qi kept his place within the team and started to showcase his penalty scoring abilities when he was designated the spot-kick taker in a league game against [[Shanghai Jiucheng]] on June 11 in a 1-1 draw.<ref name=\"China 2005\"/> After another spot-kick goal against Changchun Yatai on July 2 in a 2-1 defeat, An Qi was able to play at the highest level of Chinese football once again when top-tier side [[Xiamen Lanshi]] decided to sign him and make him their first choice goalkeeper at the beginning of the 2006 season. After two seasons with the team the club would be relegated from the Chinese Super League and decide to disband in a disappointing 2007 league season. Without a club, An Qi moved to reigning league champions Changchun Yatai where he played understudy to [[Zong Lei]]; however, before he could challenge for the goalkeeper position he suffered a knee ligament break. He went to [[Belgium]] to receive surgery, causing him to miss the entire 2008 league season. An Qi made his debut for Changchun Yatai in a league game against [[Shenzhen Asia Travel]] on 12 September 2009 in a 4\u20130 defeat.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csldata.sports.sohu.com/gameinfo.php?season=2009&gameid=A22169 |title=\u6bd4\u8d5b\u7ed3\u679c-\u4e2d\u8d85\u6570\u636e\u5e93-\u641c\u72d0 |publisher=Csldata.sports.sohu.com |date= |accessdate=2010-12-22}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nAn Qi was called up to the Chinese U20 team that played in the 2001 FIFA World Youth Championship as the starting goalkeeper for the team, which finished in the last 16. After the tournament the Chinese manager [[Bora Milutinovi\u0107]] decided to hand An Qi his senior debut in a friendly against [[Trinidad and Tobago national football team|Trinidad and Tobago]] on August 5, 2001 where he came on as a substitute for [[Jiang Jin]] in a 3-0 victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://teamchina.freehostia.com/match.php?lang=en&date=2001-08-05|title=China PR 3-0 Trinidad and Tobago |publisher=teamchina.freehostia.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref> After the friendly Bora Milutinovi\u0107 gave An Qi his competitive debut against [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]] in a [[2002 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 AFC Second Round|2002 FIFA World Cup qualification game]] on September 15, 2001 that China won 2-0.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://teamchina.freehostia.com/match.php?lang=en&date=2001-09-15|title=China PR 2-0 Uzbekistan|publisher=teamchina.freehostia.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref> After several further appearances Bora Milutinovi\u0107 decided to include him in the Chinese national squad that played during the [[2002 FIFA World Cup]].<ref name=\"WC profile\"/>\n\n==Personal life==\nOn August 14, 2005 An Qi was arrested in suspicion of rape after a night out drinking with his teammates. A woman accused him of rape at his hotel after the police responded to an alarm. After several hours of questioning the police released An Qi after there was a lack of evidence.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://zt-hzrb.hangzhou.com.cn/system/2009/09/04/010167169.shtml |title=\u5b89\u7426\u4e8b\u4ef6\u5973\u4e3b\u89d2\u53e3\u8ff0:\u4ed6\u903c\u6211\u53d1\u751f\u6027\u5173\u7cfb\u6478\u6211\u80f8\u90e8(\u56fe)-\u65b0\u95fb |publisher=Zt-hzrb.hangzhou.com.cn |accessdate=2010-12-22 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/66M1lM1rI?url=http://zt-hzrb.hangzhou.com.cn/system/2009/09/04/010167169.shtml |archive-date=2012-03-22 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n'''[[Dalian Shide]]'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/player/1467/Qi_An.html|title=An, Qi|publisher=National-football-teams.com|date=2019-08-29|accessdate=2019-08-29}}</ref>\n*[[Chinese Jia-A League]]: [[Chinese Jia-A League 2000|2000]], [[Chinese Jia-A League 2001|2001]], [[Chinese Jia-A League 2002|2002]]\n*[[Chinese FA Cup]]: [[2001 Chinese FA Cup|2001]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{NFT player|pid=1467}}\n*[http://www.sodasoccer.com/search/player/7/12179/66B9B39B447A25D2.shtml Player profiles] at Sodasoccer.com\n\n{{China Squad 2002 World Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:An, Qi}}\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers who have scored]]\n[[Category:Chinese footballers]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Dalian]]\n[[Category:China international footballers]]\n[[Category:2002 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Dalian Shide F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Xiamen Blue Lions players]]\n[[Category:Changchun Yatai F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Chinese Super League players]]\n[[Category:China League One players]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2002 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Asian Games competitors for China]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Chinese footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| image =\n| name                = An Qi<br />\u5b89\u7426\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1981|6|21}}\n| birth_place = [[Dalian]], [[Liaoning]], [[People's Republic of China|China]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.91}}\n| position            = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| youthyears1 = 1997\u20131998\n| youthclubs1 = [[Harbin Yiteng|Dalian Yiteng]]\n| years1 = 1999\u20132000 \n| years2 = 2000\u20132004 \n| years3 = 2004\u20132005 \n| years4 = 2006\u20132007 \n| years5 = 2008\u20132010\n| clubs1 = [[Guangzhou Songri]] \n| clubs2 = [[Dalian Shide]] \n| clubs3 = [[Dalian Changbo]] \n| clubs4 = [[Xiamen Lanshi]] \n| clubs5 = [[Changchun Yatai]]\n| caps1 = 2  \n| caps2 = 68  \n| caps3 = 15  \n| caps4 = 43  \n| caps5 = 1  \n| goals1 = 0  \n| goals2 = 0  \n| goals3 = 2  \n| goals4 = 0  \n| goals5 = 0 \n| totalcaps = 129 \n| totalgoals = 2\n| nationalyears1 = 2001\n| nationalteam1 = [[China national under-20 football team|China U20]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 4  \n| nationalgoals1 = 0 \n| nationalyears2 = 2001\u20132004\n| nationalteam2 = [[China national football team|China]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 9  \n| nationalgoals2 = 0 \n| pcupdate            = 6 March 2013\n| ntupdate            = 6 March 2013\n}}\n\n{{Chinese name|[[An (surname)|An]]}}\n{{about|the football player|the Chinese female poet|An Qi (poet)}}\n\n'''An Qi''' ({{zh|c=\u5b89\u7426|p=\u0100n Q\u00ed}}) (born 21 June 1981 in [[Dalian]], [[Liaoning]], [[People's Republic of China|China]]) is a former [[Chinese people|Chinese]] international association football goalkeeper. He represented [[Guangzhou Songri]], [[Dalian Shide]], [[Dalian Changbo]], [[Xiamen Lanshi]] and [[Changchun Yatai]] while internationally he participated for the [[China national football team|Chinese national team]] that took part in the [[2002 FIFA World Cup]], however he did not feature in any of the games.\n\n==Club career==\nAn Qi originally started his senior career with [[Guangzhou Songri]] before he was called up to the [[China national under-20 football team|Chinese U20 team]] that took part in the [[2001 FIFA World Youth Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=181025/index.html |title=An Qi |publisher=fifa.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref> After the tournament he was considered one of the most promising young goalkeepers within China and had already drawn the interests of reigning Chinese league champions [[Dalian Shide]] where he established himself as their first-choice goalkeeper within the 2002 league season, in time to also be called up to the [[China national football team|Chinese football team]] for the 2002 FIFA World Cup.<ref name=\"WC profile\">{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport3/worldcup2002/hi/team_pages/china/squad/newsid_1950000/1950527.stm|title=BBC World Cup profile|publisher=bbc.co.uk|date=20 May 2002|accessdate=2010-12-22}}</ref> After several 