fered a knee ligament break. He went to [[Belgium]] to receive surgery, causing him to miss the entire 2008 league season. An Qi made his debut for Changchun Yatai in a league game against [[Shenzhen Asia Travel]] on 12 September 2009 in a 4\u20130 defeat.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csldata.sports.sohu.com/gameinfo.php?season=2009&gameid=A22169 |title=\u6bd4\u8d5b\u7ed3\u679c-\u4e2d\u8d85\u6570\u636e\u5e93-\u641c\u72d0 |publisher=Csldata.sports.sohu.com |date= |accessdate=2010-12-22}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nAn Qi was called up to the Chinese U20 team that played in the 2001 FIFA World Youth Championship as the starting goalkeeper for the team, which finished in the last 16. After the tournament the Chinese manager [[Bora Milutinovi\u0107]] decided to hand An Qi his senior debut in a friendly against [[Trinidad and Tobago national football team|Trinidad and Tobago]] on August 5, 2001 where he came on as a substitute for [[Jiang Jin]] in a 3-0 victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://teamchina.freehostia.com/match.php?lang=en&date=2001-08-05|title=China PR 3-0 Trinidad and Tobago |publisher=teamchina.freehostia.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref> After the friendly Bora Milutinovi\u0107 gave An Qi his competitive debut against [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]] in a [[2002 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 AFC Second Round|2002 FIFA World Cup qualification game]] on September 15, 2001 that China won 2-0.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://teamchina.freehostia.com/match.php?lang=en&date=2001-09-15|title=China PR 2-0 Uzbekistan|publisher=teamchina.freehostia.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref> After several further appearances Bora Milutinovi\u0107 decided to include him in the Chinese national squad that played during the [[2002 FIFA World Cup]].<ref name=\"WC profile\"/>\n\n==Personal life==\nOn August 14, 2005 An Qi was arrested in suspicion of rape after a night out drinking with his teammates. A woman accused him of rape at his hotel after the police responded to an alarm. After several hours of questioning the police released An Qi after there was a lack of evidence.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://zt-hzrb.hangzhou.com.cn/system/2009/09/04/010167169.shtml |title=\u5b89\u7426\u4e8b\u4ef6\u5973\u4e3b\u89d2\u53e3\u8ff0:\u4ed6\u903c\u6211\u53d1\u751f\u6027\u5173\u7cfb\u6478\u6211\u80f8\u90e8(\u56fe)-\u65b0\u95fb |publisher=Zt-hzrb.hangzhou.com.cn |accessdate=2010-12-22 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/66M1lM1rI?url=http://zt-hzrb.hangzhou.com.cn/system/2009/09/04/010167169.shtml |archive-date=2012-03-22 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n'''[[Dalian Shide]]'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/player/1467/Qi_An.html|title=An, Qi|publisher=National-football-teams.com|date=2019-08-29|accessdate=2019-08-29}}</ref>\n*[[Chinese Jia-A League]]: [[Chinese Jia-A League 2000|2000]], [[Chinese Jia-A League 2001|2001]], [[Chinese Jia-A League 2002|2002]]\n*[[Chinese FA Cup]]: [[2001 Chinese FA Cup|2001]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{NFT player|pid=1467}}\n*[http://www.sodasoccer.com/search/player/7/12179/66B9B39B447A25D2.shtml Player profiles] at Sodasoccer.com\n\n{{China Squad 2002 World Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:An, Qi}}\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers who have scored]]\n[[Category:Chinese footballers]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Dalian]]\n[[Category:China international footballers]]\n[[Category:2002 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Dalian Shide F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Xiamen Blue Lions players]]\n[[Category:Changchun Yatai F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Chinese Super League players]]\n[[Category:China League One players]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2002 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Asian Games competitors for China]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo fixing, replaced: teams opening \u2192 team's openi